author: Mark Duell For Mailonline
title: Shocked woman finds car identical to hers parked opposite | Daily Mail Online
text: comments A woman thought she was seeing double when she spotted a car identical to hers parked opposite - and it even had the same numberplate. The motorist, who has not been identified, noticed that she had parked next to a silver Ford Kuga at Melbicks Garden Centre in Coleshill, Warwickshire. And upon closer inspection last Monday, the baffled woman realised the car - which was the same model as hers - also had the same numberplate. Same numberplate: The motorist, who has not been identified, noticed that she had parked next to a silver Ford Kuga at Melbicks Garden Centre in Coleshill, Warwickshire Matching: Upon closer inspection last Monday, the baffled woman realised the car - which was the same model as hers - also had the same numberplate She rang the police who confirmed one of the Kugas was stolen from Birmingham last year. It had been masked by copying the genuine numberplate. RELATED ARTICLES
